<li><h3><a name="f3"></a>Importing Contacts</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f3a"></a>Importing Contacts Within the “Edit Profile” Settings</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once signed in to your account, click on the “Profile” link in the upper right hand corner of the
          website.
        </li>
        <li>Click on the <%= image_tag('about/import_contacts.jpg') %> button in the “EMAIL SETTINGS” section in the
          lower right hand corner of the page.
          Our site uses the Plaxo plug in to import your contacts; you should see the following pop up once you
          click on the Import Contacts button:<br/>
          <%= image_tag('about/plaxo.jpg') %>
        </li>
        <li>Click on the radio button next to the Email Provider that you use then click "Next".</li>
        <li>Enter in your username and password and click "Sign In".</li>
        <li>Plaxo will now bring up a list of all of your contacts. You can either scroll through this list and put
          a check mark next to the contacts that you want to import, or you can just select the "Check All" option
          above the "Back" button and all of your contacts will be selected. Once you've selected all of the
          contacts you want to import, click the "Next" button. If you forget to import certain contacts or want to
          add additional contacts some time in the future, just go through these steps again.
        </li>
        <li>Plaxo should now display a message that says "Your contacts have been added". Click the "Done" button.
          Campusmack will now save all of your contacts in our protected database for easy retrieval; this might
          take a while so just wait until the website re-routes you to a page with all of your contacts listed.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f3b"></a>Importing Contacts Through the "Send as Smack" Function</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once signed in to your account, click on the <%= image_tag('about/send_as_smack_small.png') %> button on
          any Campusmack post.
        </li>
        <li>On the next page, click on the <%= image_tag('about/import_contacts.jpg') %> button beneath the
          "Message" box.
        </li>
        <li>Plaxo will now bring up a list of all of your contacts. You can either scroll through this list and put
          a check mark next to the contacts that you want to import, or you can just select the "Check All" option
          above the "Back" button and all of your contacts will be selected. Once you've selected all of the
          contacts you want to import, click the "Next" button. If you forget to import certain contacts or want to
          add additional contacts some time in the future, just go through these steps again.
        </li>
        <li>Plaxo should now display a message that says "Your contacts have been added". Click the "Done" button.
          You can now use these contacts to easily send emails to your friends. See instructions below for managing
          your contacts list and creating email groups.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ul>

</li>
<li><h3><a name="f4"></a>Managing Your Email Contacts</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f4a"></a>Creating an Email Group</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once signed in to your account, click on the “Profile” link in the upper right hand corner of the
          website.
        </li>
        <li>If you haven't already, Import your contacts using the steps outlined in the section above.</li>
        <li>Click on the <%= image_tag('about/manage_contacts.jpg') %> button in the “EMAIL SETTINGS” section in the
          lower right hand corner of the page.
        </li>
        <li>Check the boxes of the contacts you'd like to add to a group and then click
          the <%= image_tag('about/add_to_group.jpg') %> button at the top of the list of contacts
        </li>
        <li>Click the radio button next to "New Group" and then type the name of the group in the box to the right
          and click the "Add Contacts" button.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f4b"></a>Removing a Contact From a Group</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once you've added an email group, it will show up in a menu to the left of your list of contacts. To
          remove a contact from a group, click on the group you wish to remove that contact from. The site will
          display a full list of contacts included in that group.
        </li>
        <li>Click on the check box next to the contact you wish to remove from the group and then click
          the <%= image_tag('about/remove_from_group.jpg') %> button above the list of contacts. This will remove
          the contact from the group but will not delete the contact from your Contacts list.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f4c"></a>Adding a New Contact</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Click on the <%= image_tag('about/new_contact.jpg') %> button in the top right hand side of the
          "Contacts" page.
        </li>
        <li>Enter the Contact's Name and Email into the pop up and click "Submit".</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f4d"></a>Deleting a Contact</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Click on the check box next to the contact you wish to delete (you can select multiple contacts to
          delete) and then click the <%= image_tag('about/delete_selected.jpg') %> button above the list of
          contacts. This will permanently remove the contact(s) from your Contacts list.
        </li>
        <li>If you want to add this contact back in the future, you can either add it through the "New Contact" or
          "Import Contacts" feature.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f4e"></a>Editing a Contact</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Click on the <%= image_tag('about/edit.jpg') %> button to the right of the contact that you want to
          change. This will bring up a pop up box with that contact's name and email address.
        </li>
        <li>Make your changes and then click the "Submit" button.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ul>

</li>
<li><h3>Sharing Content<a name="f5"></a></h3>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f5a"></a>Send as Smack</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once you find a post you want to send_as_mack talk, click
          the <%= image_tag('about/send_as_smack_small.png') %> button. You will be routed to a landing page to
          compose the Smack email.
        </li>
        <li> If you've imported your email contacts, click the "Add Recipients" button and you'll be able to select
          groups or individual contacts to send the Smack to. Once you're done selecting contacts, click the "I'm
          Done" button next to the "To" box. You can also manually enter email addresses separated by a comma. Once
          you've finished manually entering email addresses, hit the "Tab" key.
        </li>
        <li>You can edit the default subject line to whatever you want.</li>
        <li>Type a message for the body of the email in the "Message" box.</li>
        <li>Click "Send" to send the message.</li>
        <li>Sit back and smile because you just SMACKED someone...not physically, but through the computer.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f5b"></a>Email Share</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>Once you find a post you want to share with your friends through email, click
          the <%= image_tag('about/email_share.jpg') %> icon. You will be routed to a landing page to compose the
          email.
        </li>
        <li> If you've imported your email contacts, click the "Add Recipients" button and you'll be able to select
          groups or individual contacts to share the post with. Once you're done selecting contacts, click the "I'm
          Done" button next to the "To" box. You can also manually enter email addresses separated by a comma. Once
          you've finished manually entering email addresses, hit the "Tab" key.
        </li>
        <li>You can edit the default subject line to whatever you want.</li>
        <li>Type a message for the body of the email in the "Message" box.</li>
        <li>Click "Send" to send the message.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f5c"></a>Facebook Share</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>If you find a post you want to share with your friends through Facebook, click
          the <%= image_tag('about/facebook_share.jpg') %> icon.
        </li>
        <li>Write a message in the box of the Facebook pop up and click the "Share Link" button. This will share the
          information about the Campusmack post to your Facebook wall.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4><a name="f5d"></a>Twitter Share</h4>
      <ol start="1" type="1">
        <li>If you find a post you want to share with your friends through Twitter, click
          the <%= image_tag('about/twitter_share.jpg') %> icon.
        </li>
        <li>You'll be routed to a Twitter page with a field for entering your Twitter status. The field will have an
          auto generated message from Campusmack with a link back to the post you want to share. Click "Tweet" once
          you're satisfied with the message.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ul>
</li>
</ul>
